481	\begin{remark}[Use in the cover-evaluation chain]
482	  For an affine cover $X = U_1 \cup U_2$ packaged as an \lstinline{AffineCoverMVSquare} (iter-028), the four corners of the Mayer-Vietoris square are $X_1 = U_1$, $X_2 = U_2$, $X_3 = U_1 \cap U_2$, $X_4 = \top$. The iter-029/030 LES on $\HModulePrime\,k\,(\toModuleKSheaf\,C)$ at degrees $(0, 1)$ then reads
483	  \[
484	    \HModulePrime^0(X_4) \to \HModulePrime^0(X_2) \oplus \HModulePrime^0(X_3) \to \HModulePrime^0(X_1) \to \HModulePrime^1(X_4) \to \cdots
485	  \]
486	  The iter-035 corner-bridge identifies $\HModulePrime^n(X_4)$ with $\HModule\,k\,(\toModuleKSheaf\,C)\,n$. After future affine vanishing (Mathlib gap; queued for iter-040+), $\HModulePrime^1(X_2) = \HModulePrime^1(X_3) = 0$, so the LES yields a short exact sequence presenting $\HModule^1$ as a cokernel of $\HModulePrime^0(X_2) \oplus \HModulePrime^0(X_3) \to \HModulePrime^0(X_1)$. The iter-039 curve specialisations~\ref{thm:Scheme_module_finite_HModule_zero_curve} and~\ref{thm:Scheme_module_finite_HModule_prime_zero_curve} then propagate $\Module\,k$-finiteness through the H⁰ pieces (one application per affine corner), and iter-037's \lstinline{module_finite_HModule_of_HModule'_X₄_curve} carries the result up to $\HModule\,k\,(\toModuleKSheaf\,C)\,1$, which is the genus carrier (Definition~\ref{def:genus}).
487	\end{remark}
